	<doc for="OdbcException">
		<summary>
			<para> The exception that is generated when a warning or error is returned
      by an ODBC data source. This class cannot be inherited.</para>
		</summary>
		<remarks>
			<para> This class is created whenever the
   <see cref="System.Data.Odbc.OdbcDataAdapter"/> encounters an error generated by 
      the server (Client-side errors are raised as standard common language
      runtime exceptions.). It always contains at least one instance of <see cref="System.Data.Odbc.OdbcError"/>.</para>
			<para>If the severity of the error is too great, the server may close the
   <see cref="System.Data.Odbc.OdbcConnection"/>. However, the
      user can reopen the connection and continue.</para>
		</remarks>
		<example>
			<para>The following example generates an <see cref="System.Data.Odbc.OdbcException"/>
due to a missing data source, and then displays the
exception.</para>
			<codelink SampleID="Classic WebData OdbcException" SnippetID="1"/>
		</example>
		<seealso cref="System.Data.Odbc.OdbcError"/>
		<seealso cref="System.Data.Odbc.OdbcErrorCollection"/>
	</doc>
	<doc for="OdbcException.Errors">
		<summary>
